## Module Dependency Rules

Dependencies flow **downward only**. No module may import from a module above it.

<!-- TODO: Replace with your actual dependency graph.
     Use arrow notation to show allowed dependency directions. -->

```
entry_point
  └── command_modules → shared_types, config
```

{% if stack == "rust" %}- Leaf modules (`types`, `config`) must not import from command modules.
- Use `cargo clippy` to enforce boundaries.
{% elif stack == "node" %}- Shared types live in a `types/` directory. Services do not import from routes.
- Use ESLint import rules to enforce boundaries.
{% elif stack == "python" %}- Domain modules must not import from entrypoints or adapters.
- Use import linting to enforce boundaries.
{% elif stack == "go" %}- Internal packages enforce boundaries naturally. `internal/types/` is a leaf.
- Use `go vet` and import checks to enforce boundaries.
{% else %}- Shared types are leaf dependencies — they must not import from feature modules.
- Use linting tools to enforce boundaries.
{% endif %}

